[{"text": "Buckle up.", "start": 4.971, "duration": 2.302}, {"text": "We\u2019re going to take the orbit of this rock", "start": 7.273, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "and kick it into high gear.", "start": 9.642, "duration": 2.536}, {"text": "Behold the Moon", "start": 12.178, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "breaking its planetary speed limit.", "start": 13.98, "duration": 3.871}, {"text": "The Moon orbits", "start": 39.205, "duration": 1.101}, {"text": "around our blue marble of a planet", "start": 40.306, "duration": 2.036}, {"text": "at a comfortable", "start": 42.342, "duration": 1.134}, {"text": "and reliable speed of 1 km/s (0.6 mi/s).", "start": 43.476, "duration": 4.772}, {"text": "And if that seems fast to you,", "start": 48.248, "duration": 3.003}, {"text": "well, hold on.", "start": 51.251, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "You haven\u2019t seen anything yet.", "start": 53.053, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "So how could this happen?", "start": 55.055, "duration": 3.336}, {"text": "If the Moon kept getting closer to Earth,", "start": 58.391, "duration": 3.871}, {"text": "the gravitational pull", "start": 62.262, "duration": 1.234}, {"text": "from our planet would increase.", "start": 63.496, "duration": 2.636}, {"text": "That would make the Moon\u2019s orbit", "start": 66.132, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "speed up tremendously.", "start": 68.301, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "That\u2019s the basis for Kepler\u2019s third law.", "start": 70.77, "duration": 3.804}, {"text": "So if the Moon kept creeping toward Earth,", "start": 74.574, "duration": 3.871}, {"text": "it would orbit faster and faster.", "start": 78.445, "duration": 3.97}, {"text": "And if that happened,", "start": 82.415, "duration": 2.736}, {"text": "Every 27 days, the Moon completes a trip", "start": 89.355, "duration": 3.437}, {"text": "around Earth.", "start": 92.792, "duration": 1.368}, {"text": "Well, not anymore.", "start": 94.16, "duration": 1.969}, {"text": "Get ready to see", "start": 96.129, "duration": 1.134}, {"text": "this celestial body more often.", "start": 97.263, "duration": 2.503}, {"text": "And with the Moon\u2019s increased", "start": 99.766, "duration": 1.868}, {"text": "visibility and speed,", "start": 101.634, "duration": 1.902}, {"text": "lunar eclipses would be a regular sight.", "start": 103.536, "duration": 2.836}, {"text": "But that lovely view in the sky", "start": 106.372, "duration": 3.003}, {"text": "wouldn\u2019t make up", "start": 109.375, "duration": 1.268}, {"text": "for the hell on Earth below.", "start": 110.643, "duration": 2.703}, {"text": "If the Moon moved closer,", "start": 113.346, "duration": 2.069}, {"text": "the gravitational pull", "start": 115.415, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "would rip into the Earth\u2019s crust.", "start": 117.15, "duration": 2.502}, {"text": "This increased force", "start": 119.652, "duration": 1.936}, {"text": "would create earthquakes", "start": 121.588, "duration": 1.668}, {"text": "and increase volcanic eruptions", "start": 123.256, "duration": 2.336}, {"text": "across the globe.", "start": 125.592, "duration": 1.902}, {"text": "And don\u2019t think you could", "start": 127.494, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "cool off by the ocean", "start": 129.329, "duration": 1.301}, {"text": "to escape the heat.", "start": 130.63, "duration": 1.902}, {"text": "Let me explain.", "start": 132.532, "duration": 1.501}, {"text": "The oceans ebb and flow", "start": 134.033, "duration": 1.969}, {"text": "thanks to the Moon\u2019s orbit,", "start": 136.002, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "the Earth\u2019s gravity and the Sun.", "start": 137.837, "duration": 3.203}, {"text": "So as the Moon inches closer,", "start": 141.04, "duration": 3.27}, {"text": "the ocean tides", "start": 144.31, "duration": 1.502}, {"text": "would become much larger.", "start": 145.812, "duration": 2.703}, {"text": "How large are we talking?", "start": 148.515, "duration": 3.036}, {"text": "They would be eight times\nhigher than average.", "start": 151.551, "duration": 5.038}, {"text": "Coastal cities would flood,", "start": 156.589, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "and some islands", "start": 158.324, "duration": 1.535}, {"text": "would become blanketed underwater", "start": 159.859, "duration": 2.269}, {"text": "for most of the day.", "start": 162.128, "duration": 1.635}, {"text": "Almost 700 million people ", "start": 163.763, "duration": 3.404}, {"text": "living in low-lying coastal areas", "start": 167.167, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "would be in constant danger", "start": 169.102, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "if they weren\u2019t evacuated.", "start": 171.104, "duration": 2.102}, {"text": "But what would happen", "start": 173.206, "duration": 1.535}, {"text": "if the Moon started to move", "start": 174.741, "duration": 1.668}, {"text": "even faster?", "start": 176.409, "duration": 1.935}, {"text": "Well, remember Kepler's third law?", "start": 178.344, "duration": 2.67}, {"text": "The Moon would only orbit faster", "start": 181.014, "duration": 2.669}, {"text": "if it got closer.", "start": 183.683, "duration": 1.869}, {"text": "Now, if it came", "start": 185.552, "duration": 1.101}, {"text": "within 18,470 km (11,470 mi),", "start": 186.653, "duration": 3.37}, {"text": "it would reach what's called", "start": 190.023, "duration": 1.501}, {"text": "the Roche limit.", "start": 191.524, "duration": 1.869}, {"text": "That\u2019s the point", "start": 193.393, "duration": 1.067}, {"text": "where the Moon is so close to Earth", "start": 194.46, "duration": 2.603}, {"text": "that the tidal forces between us", "start": 197.063, "duration": 2.536}, {"text": "would get strong enough", "start": 199.599, "duration": 1.401}, {"text": "to tear this grey rock apart.", "start": 201.0, "duration": 3.003}, {"text": "Thankfully,", "start": 204.003, "duration": 1.035}, {"text": "this wouldn\u2019t be able to happen.", "start": 205.038, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "Because as its speed increased,", "start": 206.773, "duration": 2.836}, {"text": "our Moon", "start": 209.609, "duration": 1.335}, {"text": "would be launched into the cosmos.", "start": 210.944, "duration": 2.836}, {"text": "Yeah, that\u2019s because", "start": 213.78, "duration": 1.635}, {"text": "once our natural satellite \nreached 1.4 km/s (0.87 mi/s),", "start": 215.415, "duration": 5.071}, {"text": "it would have enough momentum", "start": 220.486, "duration": 1.635}, {"text": "to escape Earth\u2019s gravity.", "start": 222.121, "duration": 2.937}, {"text": "As it fades from sight,", "start": 225.058, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "you might feel relieved at first.", "start": 227.527, "duration": 2.669}, {"text": "After all, the Earth\u2019s rotation", "start": 230.196, "duration": 2.302}, {"text": "would slow down without the Moon,", "start": 232.498, "duration": 1.602}, {"text": "so the days would become longer.", "start": 234.1, "duration": 3.103}, {"text": "And finally, you\u2019d see an end", "start": 237.203, "duration": 2.569}, {"text": "to the constant earthquakes", "start": 239.772, "duration": 1.669}, {"text": "and devastating floods.", "start": 241.441, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "But in reality,", "start": 243.176, "duration": 2.269}, {"text": "this is where the real nightmare begins.", "start": 245.445, "duration": 2.536}, {"text": "The tides would become smaller", "start": 247.981, "duration": 2.636}, {"text": "and weaker without the Moon.", "start": 250.617, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "Any coastal ecosystems", "start": 252.619, "duration": 1.901}, {"text": "that weren\u2019t already destroyed", "start": 254.52, "duration": 1.569}, {"text": "by the massive flooding", "start": 256.089, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "would now be completely upended.", "start": 257.924, "duration": 2.803}, {"text": "Without churning tides,", "start": 260.727, "duration": 2.502}, {"text": "animals that depend on food sources", "start": 263.229, "duration": 2.736}, {"text": "normally floating in the ocean", "start": 265.965, "duration": 2.136}, {"text": "wouldn\u2019t get the nutrients", "start": 268.101, "duration": 1.234}, {"text": "they need to live.", "start": 269.335, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "And without the Moon\u2019s light,", "start": 271.07, "duration": 2.469}, {"text": "nocturnal predators", "start": 273.539, "duration": 1.569}, {"text": "would have difficulty completing", "start": 275.108, "duration": 2.068}, {"text": "a successful hunt.", "start": 277.176, "duration": 1.836}, {"text": "This could create a mass extinction event ", "start": 279.012, "duration": 3.27}, {"text": "of creatures on land and at sea.", "start": 282.282, "duration": 3.069}, {"text": "And while life on Earth", "start": 285.351, "duration": 1.702}, {"text": "would be flipped on its ear,", "start": 287.053, "duration": 1.835}, {"text": "so would the planet.", "start": 288.888, "duration": 2.169}, {"text": "Earth has a tilt of about 23.5 degrees.", "start": 291.057, "duration": 4.438}, {"text": "This angle of its orbit", "start": 295.495, "duration": 1.668}, {"text": "makes the seasons possible.", "start": 297.163, "duration": 2.302}, {"text": "But it\u2019s the Moon\u2019s gravity", "start": 299.465, "duration": 2.369}, {"text": "that stabilizes this tilt", "start": 301.834, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "from going any further.", "start": 303.836, "duration": 1.669}, {"text": "So without it,", "start": 305.505, "duration": 1.735}, {"text": "the seasons could stop.", "start": 307.24, "duration": 2.402}, {"text": "Weather patterns might hold in place", "start": 309.642, "duration": 2.536}, {"text": "until the end of time.", "start": 312.178, "duration": 1.768}, {"text": "But if the tilt increased,", "start": 313.946, "duration": 2.503}, {"text": "it could cause", "start": 316.449, "duration": 1.401}, {"text": "extreme weather conditions.", "start": 317.85, "duration": 1.802}, {"text": "And once again,", "start": 319.652, "duration": 1.702}, {"text": "the Earth could be plunged", "start": 321.354, "duration": 1.868}, {"text": "into an ice age.", "start": 323.222, "duration": 2.002}, {"text": "Yeah, a faster lunar orbit", "start": 325.224, "duration": 3.17}, {"text": "could fast-track all life on Earth", "start": 328.394, "duration": 2.703}, {"text": "to extinction.", "start": 331.097, "duration": 2.135}, {"text": " OK, so instead of losing the Moon,", "start": 333.232, "duration": 3.437}, {"text": "what if we crowded the sky", "start": 336.669, "duration": 1.869}, {"text": "with the moons of Jupiter?", "start": 338.538, "duration": 2.135}, {"text": "Well, that\u2019s a story for another WHAT IF.", "start": 340.673, "duration": 6.273}]